2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes an approach to predict scenicness which explicitly accounts for the variance of human ratings, which involves the use of machine learning algorithms and techniques. 
3. cs.GR (Graphics) - The paper deals with outdoor images and their scenicness, which is a topic related to computer graphics. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with image processing and understanding, which is a topic related to multimedia. 
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a machine learning-based approach to predict scenicness, which falls under the category of machine learning.
